annotation.TEXT: Whoa, I thought I was going to miss the goal tape there! The hit detection on the goal tape does tend to be slightly generous.
Now I'm screwing up again...
Am I supposed to make a block factory with it?

Alright, we've got some note blocks here. And note that the note in the middle is a double-note, which notably is the bounce-on-all-sides variety. Speaking of bouncing, there are these parakoopdooders here to bounce off of...

Hmm... I think I'll be wandering in stars here...

Okay, this is clearly inspired by a particular Space Zone level of Super Mario Land 2. Also, there's a mushroom and a mushroom-pattern here.
And there's the secret exit, but what's the P-switch for?
Whoa, that was kind of close...
Aha, a pipe! Could this possibly lead to the secret exit? Maybe.
Yeah, I'm just turbo spinning while waiting here. Okay, so there's the P-switch, but is there anything further to the left?
There's a heart pattern here.
The camera makes stomping the last guy here a little tricky, but it should still be doable. Also, I want all of those coins.
Whoa, and I had a close call there.

Hello, and welcome back to Super Marina World! Now let's go straight to the voting results...
BLOCK FACTORY!!! Wow, twice in one episode, and on the first try both times! LOL at the doomed shell-less duder!
Careful. These are moving like Roto-Discs.

Umm... I have no idea why the "Shine Get!" music played a couple seconds early there. And it turns out it's like that in my original WMM project. I could've sworn I placed that sound clip correctly, so I don't know how I screwed it up and didn't notice sooner...
Hmm... A backup feather sounds like a good idea here.
Alright, see you next time! To be continued...

Yes there is...

Here's something weird: When I went to search for this song just to confirm its name, it suggested "Super Mario Land 2 Music Star Maza" to me, and after I typed "...Star Maze" instead, it asked me "Did you mean: ...Star Maza"? Is "Maza" even a word? Or is YouTube's search engine screwed up there?
Oh! Another left-bound winged ? block! Okay, I'll ride this one!

Okay, you can't star-kill the evil stars. Also, there's this passage under the goal down here, which contains a 1♥P. Be careful, though, as your invincibility will likely wear off around this point.
That unlocks 7-B to the left. Now, let's go back to 7-5 for the normal exit.

However, I'm surprised it just restarted the level instead of trapping me in the bonus game room like I was expecting (which is why I waited until I cleared the level before trying this). I wonder why the level restarted instead... Also, I'm going to assume that you flat-out die if you try this while already small.
BGM: Super Mario Land 2 - Star Maze

Okay, I've restocked on the mushrooms I lost while trying out that glitch. Now, let's see which levels are available for viewers to vote on this time...

Another feather. I find it weird how feathers that come from a winged ? block sway to the left first, but all other feathers sway to the right first.

And those are the levels you can vote for. Gasp! The number of level choices has increased since last time! However, fear not, as this is the last time that the number of level choices can possibly increase.

...Yep! Just as I thought! Walking into the evil stars from the side while I'm powered up makes them act like an exit-enabled pipe (while injuring me and taking away my reserve item). I remember raocow encountering this glitch too. What's with the glitchy custom hurt blocks in this hack?

COINS!!!
